reviews.text: Train Station is OK, is working well. But the station has a very bad company cleaning, Carlisle, the bosses are terrible creatures. That company should go away. They love and give rewards to nasty guys. See the picture, the guy in the picture attacked the van which was worked with. Colleagues and bosses forgiven him after all,  and gave to him a new van for reward!!

Some of the ticket office sales representatives can be impolite, if not rude, occasionally. Best to avoid by using the machines if possible. Also this station has two entrances. But if you want to use the manned ticket office be sure to go to the main entrance as the ticket office at the second entrance isn't always open and then only has a machine. it's a long walk back round to the main entrance.

Trains are usually on time.
Station has plenty of seating, 3 cafe's, lifts and toilets.
Always many taxis available waiting in a queue outside, also a station forecourt for buses to the town centre or surrounding towns.
Great station, with all the facilities you would expect at a typical British railway station. Could do with some more seating outside on the platforms.

Really annoying when I have to get to school in a hurry and I’m stopped for a good minute to ask how old I am. I can’t even get through the gates with a child ticket because they’re rigged to not allow them without inspection. Really annoying.
